Create A Website on GitHub 

Step-by-step:

Get a free user name at GitHub by going to github.com.
Click “Sign up” you will be directed to enter your username, email, and password. 
Click “Repositories”, and then click “new”.
Create a repository name.

Once repository has been created, create a folder where you will save 2 files in the same directory.
Using you code editor, create: index.html file containing the following code:

<html>
    <h1>YourName's Portfolio</h1>
    <img src="./YourFileName.jpg" />
</html>

Save the files using the code editor .
Drag files from folder to your GitHub’s repository or upload them.
Check by hitting your repository in the website…
 Congratulations, you have created your own web page in GitHub!! 
